# Hermetic docker build context.
#
# Both Dockerfile.selfhosted and Dockerfile.server rebuild every workspace
# package from source inside the image (`bun --filter @genfeedai/<pkg> build`).
# A clean CI checkout has no build artifacts (dist/, *.tsbuildinfo, node_modules
# are all gitignored), so the in-image source builds are the source of truth.
#
# On a developer machine those artifacts DO exist on disk, and without this file
# `COPY packages/ packages/` would drag stale host artifacts into the image,
# diverging from CI. The concrete failure: @genfeedai/enums is a composite
# `tsc --build` project whose buildinfo lives at packages/enums/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
# (outside dist/). A leaked, "up to date" buildinfo makes `tsc --build` skip the
# dist emit, so @genfeedai/integrations' `references: [{ path: "../enums" }]`
# resolves to a missing packages/enums/dist/index.d.ts and aborts with TS6305.
# Excluding the artifacts below keeps the context identical to a fresh checkout.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# VCS metadata and local env / secrets must never enter the build context.
.git
.gitignore
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Editor / OS cruft
**/.DS_Store
